Getting Started
pacman is a R package management tool. It provides intuitively named functions for the base functions. The code chunk below installs and loads sf and tidyverse packages into R environment:

pacman::p_load(sf, tidyverse)

An alternate way to install and import the libraries is as follows:

packages = c('sf','tidyverse')
for (p in packages){
  if(!require(p, character.only = T)){
    install.packages(p)
  }
  library(p, character.only = T)
}
